caption: I don't need your approval. I just need you to tie the laces.
It’s genius! They’ll be tracking 2 men on foot!
I don't think 'dressage' means what you think it means.
Dude, I'm a horse and I'm talking and the first question you ask is, why I am wearing shoes that don't match?
Technically, they're still horseshoes.
Because they don't need to be nailed to my feet, that's why.
You should talk.  Look at that hat.
I couldn't decide between the ruby slippers and the blue suede shoes, and then realized I didn't have to.
No, I didn’t get my bangs cut. Something else. Think.
I think that will be our last visit to Rodeo Drive.
I'm going as two people in a horse costume.
My horse sense said ‘whoa’ but my fashion sense said ‘giddy-up.’
You have redefined ranch dressing.
Yeah?..Well, I think your hat looks stupid!
I was really hoping for Saddle Shoes.
Did I just hear a discouraging word?
Sure Jed, act like you haven’t also been ordering things you don’t need on Amazon...
If we pull this off, there’ll be one confused posse searching the desert for a couple of eight hundred pound women.
The front ones are for work.  The back ones are just for kicks.
Your hat looks ridiculous
Sorry, I’m no longer that horse you rode in on.
I'm guessing by the look of it this is your first rodeo.
You know what they say: Dress for the job you want, not for the job you have.
Sure, but don't expect me to get above a canter until I break these in.
It was a spur of the moment purchase.
Oh, you're home early.
People change, Dave.
Slip-ons vs nail-ons, which would you choose?
His suspicions proved true once he saw the shoes. She was a night mare.
It's called dressing for the job you WANT.
